		<body.head>
			<hedline><hl1>Coyotes 5, Penguins 4</hl1></hedline>
			<byline>By <person>MEL REISNER</person>
			<byttl>AP Sports Writer</byttl>
			</byline>
		</body.head>
		<body.content>
			<p>PHOENIX (AP) - The crowd that cheered Mario Lemieux in his only visit to
			Phoenix got behind the home team at the end.</p>
			<p>Nearly all the fans were on their feet during a six-goal third period in
			which the lead changed hands three times and the Coyotes got three of their
			four power-play goals.</p>
			<p>The last - Keith Tkachuk's second and NHL-leading 14th - was enough to earn
			the Coyotes a 5-4 victory over Lemieux's Pittsburgh Penguins on Wednesday
			night.</p>
